Johannesburg Water announced on Monday that some of its reservoirs and towers were running dry as a result of pumping challenges, and said the Sandton and Midrand areas were  affected. “It is anticipated other areas will also be affected,” said  spokesperson Nondumiso Mabuza. She said the entity will communicate more information once it becomes available. Johannesburg Water   was also investigating the cause of a water outage in Riverlea in southern Johannesburg on Monday morning, she added. TimesLIVE